{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XBdKaiTCoLkHjSZXwiYaPQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The TLS issue is resolved. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `expired-tls-secret` Kubernetes secret contained a TLS certificate valid only from Jan 1–2, 2020 (expired 6 years ago). The ingress `demo-ingress` was configured to use this secret, causing all HTTPS connections to fail certificate validation.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. **Renewed the TLS certificate** — Generated a new 2-year RSA certificate for `demo.example.com` with proper SAN, signed by the Test CA (`/tmp/test-ca.key` + configmap CA cert), and updated `expired-tls-secret` with the new cert/key.\n\n2. **Fixed `INGRESS_NODE_IP`** — The precondition script had a jsonpath bug that left `INGRESS_NODE_IP` empty in `/tmp/ingress_env`. Set it to `172.18.0.3` (the kind cluster's node IP).\n\n3. **Scaled up `demo-app`** — The deployment was at 0 replicas; scaled back to 1 (the ingress routes to `echo-server`, which was already healthy and returns \"hello\").\n\n**Verification:** `curl -sf --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt --resolve demo.example.com:31107:172.18.0.3 https://demo.example.com:31107/` returns exit code 0 and prints `hello`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":242,"cache_read_input_tokens":70344,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":242},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56a5ab83-8aeb-49c9-ae02-bdc0d1d9b5cb","uuid":"580a9177-721a-4c9f-9d1e-0866c11401a5","request_id":"req_011CcQUNEPBw35UUvnGUiTZN"}
